André Myhrer.label: André Myhrer
André Myhrer.description: André Myhrer is a World Cup alpine ski racer and Olympic medalist from Sweden. Born in Bergsjö in Gävleborg County, Myhrer competes in the technical events and specialises in slalom. Wikipedia

Billy Kidd.label: Billy Kidd
Billy Kidd.description: William Winston "Billy" Kidd is a former alpine ski racer, and a member of the U.S. Ski Team from 1962-70. Wikipedia

Debbie Armstrong.label: Debbie Armstrong
Debbie Armstrong.description: Deborah Rae "Debbie" Armstrong is a former World Cup alpine ski racer from Seattle, Washington. She was the first gold medalist from the U.S. in women's alpine skiing in 12 years, winning the giant ... Wikipedia

Ingemar Stenmark.label: Ingemar Stenmark
Ingemar Stenmark.description: Jan Ingemar Stenmark is a Swedish former skier, active during the 1970s and 1980s. He is regarded as one of the most prominent Swedish sportsmen, and as the greatest slalom and giant slalom specialist of all time. Wikipedia

Jimmie Heuga.label: Jimmie Heuga
Jimmie Heuga.description: James Frederic "Jimmie" Heuga was an American alpine ski racer who became one of the first two members of the U.S. men's team to win an Olympic medal in his sport. Wikipedia
Jimmie Heuga.Born: September 22, 1943, San Francisco, California, United States

Pernilla Wiberg.label: Pernilla Wiberg
Pernilla Wiberg.description: Pernilla Wiberg is a Swedish former alpine ski racer, who competed on the World Cup circuit between 1990 and 2002, where she became one of the few all-event winners. Wikipedia

Spider Sabich.label: Spider Sabich
Spider Sabich.description: Vladimir Peter Sabich, Jr. was an American alpine ski racer. He was a member of the U.S. Ski Team on the World Cup circuit in the late 1960s and competed at the 1968 Winter Olympics; he was the pro ski ... Wikipedia

Chiara Costazza.label: Chiara Costazza
Chiara Costazza.description:
Chiara Costazza is an Italian Alpine skier.
She was born in Cavalese, Trentino, and resides in Pozza di Fassa. She won her first World Cup race, a slalom, in December 2007 at Lienz, Austria. She competed at the 2006 and 2010 in the slalom event. Wikipedia

Hiroya Saito.label: Hiroya Saito
Hiroya Saito.description:
Hiroya Saito is a former Japanese ski jumper.
He competed from 1991 to 2002. He won a gold medal at the 1998 Winter Olympics in Nagano in the Team large hill event. Wikipedia

Kristina Koznick.label: Kristina Koznick
Kristina Koznick.description: Kristina Lyn Koznick is a former World Cup alpine ski racer from the United States. She raced in the technical events and specialized in slalom. Wikipedia
Kristina Koznick.Born: November 24, 1975 (age 38), Apple Valley, Minnesota, United States

Mario Innauer.label: Mario Innauer
Mario Innauer.description:
Mario Innauer is a former Austrian ski jumper. He is the son of the legendary Austrian ski jumper and Olympic gold medalist Toni Innauer.
Mario Innauer 'avbest World Cup result was reached in 2007 in Titisee-Neustadt, where he came in fifth. Wikipedia

Rosi Mittermaier.label: Rosi Mittermaier
Rosi Mittermaier.description: Rosemarie "Rosi" Mittermaier-Neureuther is a retired World Cup alpine ski racer from Germany. She was the overall World Cup champion in 1976 and a double gold medalist at the 1976 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Ana Jelušić.label: Ana Jelušić
Ana Jelušić.description:
Ana Jelušić is a former World Cup alpine ski racer from Croatia.
Born in Rijeka, at the time SR Croatia, SFR Yugoslavia, Jelušić specialized in slalom and competed in the 2002 Winter Olympics at age 15, the youngest competitor at those games. Wikipedia

Andreas Küttel.label: Andreas Küttel
Andreas Küttel.description: Andreas Küttel is a Swiss former ski jumper. He grew up in Einsiedeln. He won the World Cup competitions on 3 December 2005 in Lillehammer and on 9 December 2005 in Harrachov and placed third in the overall championship. Wikipedia

Anssi Koivuranta.label: Anssi Koivuranta
Anssi Koivuranta.description: Anssi Koivuranta is a ski jumper and former nordic combined skier from Finland. Known for winning the 2008–09 FIS Nordic Combined World Cup. Wikipedia

Dimitry Vassiliev.label: Dimitry Vassiliev
Dimitry Vassiliev.description: Dimitry Viktorovich Vassiliev is a Russian ski jumper who has been competing in the World Cup since 1999. Wikipedia

Hannes Reichelt.label: Hannes Reichelt
Hannes Reichelt.description:
Johannes "Hannes" Reichelt is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Austria. He competes in Downhill, Super G, Giant Slalom, and Combined.
Born in Altenmarkt im Pongau in Salzburg, Reichelt made his World Cup debut in December 2001. Wikipedia

Horst Bulau.label: Horst Bulau
Horst Bulau.description:
Horst Bulau is a former Canadian ski jumper who competed from 1979 to 1992.
By the end of his career, he had thirteen World Cup wins to his credit, the most by any skier in Canadian history during that time period. Wikipedia

Jens Salumäe.label: Jens Salumäe
Jens Salumäe.description: Jens Salumäe is an Estonian retired ski jumper and nordic combined skier who has been competing since 2002. He finished 23rd in the individual large hill event at the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin. Wikipedia

Jure Košir.label: Jure Košir
Jure Košir.description: Jure Košir is a Slovenian former alpine skier. Wikipedia

Manfred Mölgg.label: Manfred Mölgg
Manfred Mölgg.description: Manfred Mölgg is a World Cup alpine ski racer from northern Italy. He specializes in the technical events of slalom and giant slalom. Wikipedia

Manuela Mölgg.label: Manuela Mölgg
Manuela Mölgg.description: Manuela Mölgg is World Cup alpine ski racer from northern Italy, a specialist in the technical events of slalom and giant slalom. Mölgg has ten World Cup podium finishes and appeared in two Olympics and four World Championships. Wikipedia

Masahiko Harada.label: Masahiko Harada
Masahiko Harada.description: Masahiko Harada is a Japanese ski jumper. He is best remembered for a meltdown at the 1994 Winter Olympics in Lillehammer and his subsequent redemption at the 1998 Winter Olympics in Nagano. Wikipedia

Matti Hautamäki.label: Matti Hautamäki
Matti Hautamäki.description:
Matti Antero Hautamäki is a former Finnish ski jumper.
Matti made his first ski-jumping attempts at the age of seven near his home town of Oulu. When his older brother Jussi and his friend Lauri Hakola moved to Kuopio, Matti followed them. Wikipedia

Petter Tande.label: Petter Tande
Petter Tande.description: Petter Laukslett Tande is a Norwegian nordic combined skier who has been competing since 2002, representing Byåsen IL. He has three medals in the 4 x 5 km team event at the FIS Nordic World Ski Championships, with a gold and two bronzes. Wikipedia

René Sommerfeldt.label: René Sommerfeldt
René Sommerfeldt.description: René Sommerfeldt is a German cross-country skier who competed from 1994 to 2010. He won 2 medals in the 4 x 10 km relays at the Winter Olympics with a silver in 2006 and a bronze in 2002. Wikipedia

Régine Cavagnoud.label: Régine Cavagnoud
Régine Cavagnoud.description: Régine Cavagnoud was a World Cup alpine ski racer from France. She was the World Cup and World Champion in Super G in 2001. Later that year, Cavagnoud was involved in a high-speed collision while training and died two days later. Wikipedia

Rok Petrovič.label: Rok Petrovič
Rok Petrovič.description:
Rok Petrovič was a Slovenian alpine skier.
Petrovič was born in Ljubljana, Slovenia, the son of Krešimir Petrović, a well known sports psychologist of Croatian origin. Wikipedia

Primož Peterka.label: Primož Peterka
Primož Peterka.description: Primož Peterka is a Slovenian former ski jumper. He has won 15 World Cup events, making him the third most successful Slovenian winter sports athlete and one of the most successful Slovenian sports personalities. Wikipedia

Werner Heel.label: Werner Heel
Werner Heel.description:
Werner Heel is a World Cup alpine ski racer from northern Italy.
Born in Meran, Heel grew up in St. Leonhard in Passeier and currently resides in Meran, where he works as a police officer. He began skiing at the age of four. Wikipedia

Alexey Poltoranin.label: Alexey Poltoranin
Alexey Poltoranin.description: Alexey Yurevich Poltoranin is a Kazakh cross-country skier who has competed at the international senior level since 2004. He has three world cup wins, one in 2010 and two in 2013. Wikipedia

Andreas Stjernen.label: Andreas Stjernen
Andreas Stjernen.description:
Andreas Kolset Stjernen is a Norwegian ski jumper.
He made his debut in the Continental Cup in February 2005 in Brotterode, scoring two 49th places over two days. Wikipedia

Coline Mattel.label: Coline Mattel
Coline Mattel.description: Coline Mattel is a French ski jumper. In World Championships in Oslo 2011 she took 3rd place. In World Cup she debuted on 3 December 2011 in Lillehammer where she took 2nd place, her first World Cup podium. Wikipedia

Eva Logar.label: Eva Logar
Eva Logar.description:
Eva Logar is a Slovenian ski jumper, who represents the club SD Zabrdje.
Her biggest career result was fourth place individual in the 2011 World Championship in Oslo at normal hill. Wikipedia

Felix Schoft.label: Felix Schoft
Felix Schoft.description:
Felix Schoft is a German ski jumper.
In the World Cup he finished once among the top 20, with a seventeenth place from Pragelato in December 2008. Wikipedia

Fränzi Aufdenblatten.label: Fränzi Aufdenblatten
Fränzi Aufdenblatten.description:
Franziska Christine "Fränzi" Aufdenblatten is a retired Swiss World Cup alpine ski racer.
Born in Zermatt, Valais, Aufdenblatten made her World Cup debut in March 2000 in a giant slalom at Sestriere. Wikipedia

Ilka Štuhec.label: Ilka Štuhec
Ilka Štuhec.description:
Ilka Štuhec is a Slovenian alpine skier. She is a three times FIS Junior World Champion in three different disciplines.
At 2007 FIS Junior World Ski Championships she won two gold slalom combined medals in Flachau, Austria. Wikipedia

Isak Grimholm.label: Isak Grimholm
Isak Grimholm.description:
Isak Grimholm is a Swedish ski jumper.
He made his Continental Cup debut in August 2002 in Marikollen, and his best result is a victory from Iron Mountain in February 2007. He participated in the FIS Junior World Ski Championships in 2002 and 2003. Wikipedia

Jurij Tepeš.label: Jurij Tepeš
Jurij Tepeš.description: Jurij Tepeš is a Slovenian ski jumper. His father Miran Tepeš was also a ski jumper, now he is a technical delegate at FIS World Cup ski jumping events. His sister Anja Tepeš is also a ski jumper competing in Women's ski jumping world cup. Wikipedia

Kaarel Nurmsalu.label: Kaarel Nurmsalu
Kaarel Nurmsalu.description:
Kaarel Nurmsalu is a ski jumper, formerly nordic combined skier from Estonia.
He won 3 individual bronze medals at the 2011 Nordic Junior World Ski Championships in Otepää.
He holds the national record of Estonia in ski-flying with 204m. Wikipedia

Karianne Bjellånes.label: Karianne Bjellånes
Karianne Bjellånes.description:
Karianne Gåsland Bjellånes is a Norwegian cross-country skier. She represents Henning SL, and lives in Trondheim.
She made her World Cup debut in March 2007 in Drammen, and collected her first World Cup points in that race with a 27th place. Wikipedia

Kwame Nkrumah-Acheampong.label: Kwame Nkrumah-Acheampong
Kwame Nkrumah-Acheampong.description: Kwame Nkrumah-Acheampong, nicknamed "The Snow Leopard", is a Ghanaian skier and is the first person from Ghana to take part in the Winter Olympics, which he did at the 2010 Winter Olympics Vancouver, British Columbia. taking part in the slalom. Wikipedia

Kim Rene Elverum Sorsell.label: Kim Rene Elverum Sorsell
Kim Rene Elverum Sorsell.description:
Kim Rene Elverum Sorsell is a Norwegian ski jumper.
He made his debut in the World Cup in December 2007 in Trondheim, where he finished 43rd. Wikipedia

Lukáš Hlava.label: Lukáš Hlava
Lukáš Hlava.description: Lukáš Hlava is a Czech ski jumper who has competed since 2002. At the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver, he finished seventh in the team large hill and 38th in the individual normal hill events. Wikipedia

Maja Vtič.label: Maja Vtič
Maja Vtič.description:
Maja Vtič is a Slovenian ski jumper, who represents the club SD Zabrdje. She lives in Mirna, central Slovenia.
In 2007, she won bronze at the Junior World Ski Championship in Tarvisio, Italy. She placed fifth in the 2011 World Championship in Oslo. Wikipedia

Marcel Mathis.label: Marcel Mathis
Marcel Mathis.description: Marcel Mathis is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Austria. Born in Hohenems, Vorarlberg, he primarily competes on the European Cup circuit, but has raced in several World Cup events, all in giant slalom. Wikipedia

Patrick Biggs.label: Patrick Biggs
Patrick Biggs.description:
Patrick Biggs is a Canadian alpine skier.
Biggs has twice finished in the top 10 in the slalom at World Cup events, both in 2005 and has won multiple medals at the Canadian championships in slalom. Wikipedia

Richard Freitag.label: Richard Freitag
Richard Freitag.description:
Richard Freitag is a German ski jumper.
His FIS Ski Jumping World Cup debut took place on 29 December 2009 at the Four Hills Tournament in Oberstdorf, having previously gained success in the Continental Cup. Wikipedia

Rune Velta.label: Rune Velta
Rune Velta.description:
Rune Velta, is a Norwegian ski jumper.
On 25 February 2012, Velta finished second in the World Skiflying Championship in Vikersund behind Robert Kranjec. He made his debut in the World Cup in March 2010 in Oslo, where he finished 43rd. Wikipedia

Sara Takanashi.label: Sara Takanashi
Sara Takanashi.description: Sara Takanashi is a Japanese ski jumper. Wikipedia

Severin Freund.label: Severin Freund
Severin Freund.description:
Severin Freund is a German ski jumper. He hails from Waldkirchen.
Having made his Continental Cup debut in December 2004, his best result is the victory from Lillehammer in September 2008. Wikipedia

Stacey Cook.label: Stacey Cook
Stacey Cook.description: Stacey Janelle Cook is a World Cup alpine ski racer from the United States, and specializes in the speed events. Wikipedia

Stefano Gross.label: Stefano Gross
Stefano Gross.description: Stefano Gross is a World Cup alpine ski racer from northern Italy. Born in Bolzano in South Tyrol, he skis the technical events and specializes in the slalom. Wikipedia

Veronika Šarec.label: Veronika Šarec
Veronika Šarec.description:
Veronika Šarec is a former alpine skier.
In her career, Šarec won one Alpine Skiing World Cup Slalom race, with seven podiums altogether. Her only win was the Haus im Ennstal Slalom in the 1989/90 season. Wikipedia

Vladimir Zografski.label: Vladimir Zografski
Vladimir Zografski.description: Vladimir Zografski, born 14 July 1993 in Samokov, Bulgaria is a Bulgarian ski jumper. He took a 43rd place in the K-90 Normal hill competition in the FIS Nordic World Ski Championships 2009 in Liberec, Czech Republic. Wikipedia

Andréa Zimmermann.label: Andréa Zimmermann
Andréa Zimmermann.description:
Andréa Ursina Zimmermann from Monthey is a Swiss ski mountaineer and mountain runner.
Zimmermann was born in Biel/Bienne. She competed first in the 2000 Trophée du Muveran race and has been member of the national team since 2001. Wikipedia

Christian Bruder.label: Christian Bruder
Christian Bruder.description:
Christian Bruder is a retired German ski jumper.
In the World Cup he finished once among the top 15, his best result being a fourteenth place from Sapporo in February 2005.
He also participated in Nordic combined, but not in World Cup events. Wikipedia

Gaudenzio Godioz.label: Gaudenzio Godioz
Gaudenzio Godioz.description: Gaudenzio Godioz is an Italian cross country skier who competed from 1992 to 2000. His best World Cup finish was sixth twice, both in the 30 km events with one each in 1992 and in 1995. Wikipedia

Olav Tronvoll.label: Olav Tronvoll
Olav Tronvoll.description: Olav Tronvoll is a Norwegian ski mountaineer. Wikipedia

Fabien Anselmet.label: Fabien Anselmet
Fabien Anselmet.description: Fabien Anselmet is a French ski mountaineer and skiing instructor. Wikipedia

Carolina Ruiz Castillo.label: Carolina Ruiz Castillo
Carolina Ruiz Castillo.description: Carolina Ruiz Castillo is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Spain. Born in Osorno, Chile, she has represented Spain in four Winter Olympics and eight World Championships. Wikipedia

Łukasz Rutkowski.label: Łukasz Rutkowski
Łukasz Rutkowski.description: Łukasz Rutkowski is a Polish ski jumper. Wikipedia

Arnold Andenmatten.label: Arnold Andenmatten
Arnold Andenmatten.description: Arnold Andenmatten is a Swiss skier and skiing instructor. Wikipedia

Arnold Käch.label: Arnold Käch
Arnold Käch.description: Arnold Käch was a Swiss military officer, skier, ski official and writer. Wikipedia

Bronisław Czech.label: Bronisław Czech
Bronisław Czech.description: Bronisław "Bronek" Czech was a Polish sportsman and artist. A gifted skier, he won championships of Poland 24 times in various skiing disciplines, including Alpine skiing, Nordic skiing and ski jumping. Wikipedia

David Zogg.label: David Zogg
David Zogg.description:
David Zogg was a Swiss alpine and Nordic combined skier. He was raised in Arosa, Switzerland.
At the 1928 Winter Olympics in St. Moritz he finished 16th in the Nordic combined event. Wikipedia

Fabienne Suter.label: Fabienne Suter
Fabienne Suter.description: Fabienne Suter is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Switzerland. Born in Sattel in the canton of Schwyz, she specializes in the Super G, giant slalom, and the downhill. Wikipedia

Franz Heinzer.label: Franz Heinzer
Franz Heinzer.description: Franz Heinzer is a former alpine ski racer, who specialized in downhill. He was World Cup champion in downhill three consecutive seasons, second only to Franz Klammer. Wikipedia

Krzysztof Miętus.label: Krzysztof Miętus
Krzysztof Miętus.description: Krzysztof Miętus is a Polish ski jumper who has competed since 2008. He is a member of Polish youth team, he participated in the Olympics in Vancouver 2010. Wikipedia

Marc Gini.label: Marc Gini
Marc Gini.description:
Marc Gini is a Swiss alpine skier, specializing in slalom and giant slalom.
He started his career in 2000, and has competed in World Cup races since 2003. Wikipedia

Maria Pietilä Holmner.label: Maria Pietilä Holmner
Maria Pietilä Holmner.description:
Maria Helena Pietilä-Holmner is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Sweden. She specializes in the technical events of slalom and giant slalom.
Born in Umeå, Pietilä-Holmner made her World Cup debut at age 16 in October 2002. Wikipedia

Otto Furrer.label: Otto Furrer
Otto Furrer.description:
Otto Furrer was a Swiss alpine skier and cross-country skier and world champion.
Furrer was born in Zermatt. Wikipedia

Per Elofsson.label: Per Elofsson
Per Elofsson.description: Per Eilert Elofsson is a Swedish cross-country skier who competed from 1997 to 2004. He won a bronze medal in the 10 km + 10 km combined pursuit at the 2002 Winter Olympics in Salt Lake City. Wikipedia

Piotr Żyła.label: Piotr Żyła
Piotr Żyła.description: Piotr Żyła is a Polish ski jumper who has competed since 2004. A member of the national team. He has competed in the 2014 Winter Olympics in Sochi. On January 26, 2013 he became the Polish record holder in the length of the ski flight. Wikipedia

Piotr Fijas.label: Piotr Fijas
Piotr Fijas.description:
Piotr Fijas was a Polish ski jumper who competed from 1979 to 1988.
He won a bronze medal at the FIS Ski-Flying World Championships 1979 in Planica, Yugoslavia. Wikipedia

Primož Pikl.label: Primoz Pikl
Primož Pikl.description: Primož Pikl is a Slovenian ski jumper who has competed since 2002. At the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver, he finished eighth in the team large hill and 24th in the individual normal hill events. Wikipedia

Rafał Śliż.label: Rafał Śliż
Rafał Śliż.description:
Rafał Śliż is a Polish ski jumper.
He made his Continental Cup debut in January 2004, his best result being a first place from Sapporo in January 2006 as well as two victories in Rovaniemi in December 2006. Wikipedia

Roland Collombin.label: Roland Collombin
Roland Collombin.description: Roland Collombin is a former World Cup alpine ski racer from Switzerland, a two-time World Cup downhill champion and Olympic silver medalist. Wikipedia

Władysław Żytkowicz.label: Władysław Żytkowicz
Władysław Żytkowicz.description: Władysław Żytkowicz was a Polish soldier and skier. Wikipedia

Tobias Grünenfelder.label: Tobias Grünenfelder
Tobias Grünenfelder.description: Tobias Grünenfelder is a Swiss alpine skier. He is the 2005, 2006, 2009 and 2010 Swiss champion in Super-G. He also won national Downhill gold in 2007 and 2009. Wikipedia

Wojciech Skupień.label: Wojciech Skupień
Wojciech Skupień.description: Wojciech Skupień is a Polish ski jumper who has been competing since 1993. At the 1998 Winter Olympics in Nagano, he finished eighth in the team large hill and 11th in the individual large hill events. Wikipedia

Patrick Deneen.label: Patrick Deneen
Patrick Deneen.description: Patrick Deneen is an American freestyle skier, specializing in moguls. Deneen was the gold medalist at the 2009 International Ski Federation Freestyle World Ski Championships. Wikipedia
Patrick Deneen.Born: December 25, 1987 (age 26), Snoqualmie Pass, Washington, United States

Rok Perko.label: Rok Perko
Rok Perko.description: Rok Perko is a Slovenian alpine ski racer. He is specialized in downhill, super-G and combined. Wikipedia

Jonna Mendes.label: Jonna Mendes
Jonna Mendes.description: Jonna Mendes is a former World Cup alpine ski racer from the United States. She specialized in the speed events and raced for nine seasons on the World Cup circuit. Mendes competed in two Winter Olympics and four World Championships. Wikipedia
Jonna Mendes.Born: March 21, 1979 (age 35), Santa Cruz, California, United States

Vinko Bogataj.label: Vinko Bogataj
Vinko Bogataj.description: Vinko Bogataj is a former ski jumper from Slovenia who became noted on US television in the 1970s for a moment of spectacular failure that was featured on ABC's Wide World of Sports as the infamous Agony of Defeat. Wikipedia

Herbert Leupold.label: Herbert Leupold
Herbert Leupold.description:
Herbert Leupold was a German cross country skier and biathlete who competed in the 1930s.
Leupold was born in Wüstewaltersdorf. He was killed during World War II in Navaginskaya, Krasnodar Krai. Wikipedia
Herbert Leupold.Born: June 20, 1908, Walim, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, Poland

Susan Corrock.label: Susan Corrock
Susan Corrock.description: Susan Corrock Luby is a former World Cup alpine ski racer, a member of the U.S. Ski Team in the early 1970s. Talented in all three disciplines, she had 16 top ten finishes in World Cup competition 8 in downhill, 2 in giant slalom, and 6 in slalom. Wikipedia

Michael von Grünigen.label: Michael von Grünigen
Michael von Grünigen.description: Michael von Grünigen is a Swiss former alpine skier. In 1996, 1997, 1999 and 2003, he won the World Cup in Giant Slalom. In 1997 and 2001, he was World Champion in Giant Slalom. Wikipedia

Anders Fannemel.label: Anders Fannemel
Anders Fannemel.description:
Anders Fannemel, is a Norwegian ski jumper.
He made his debut in the Continental Cup in September 2008 in Lillehammer, scoring two seventh places over two days. Wikipedia

Benjamin Thomsen.label: Benjamin Thomsen
Benjamin Thomsen.description: Benjamin Thomsen is a World Cup alpine ski racer from Canada. Born in Invermere, British Columbia, he primarily competes in the speed events of Downhill and Super G. Thomsen made his World Cup debut in ... Wikipedia

Fritz Dopfer.label: Fritz Dopfer
Fritz Dopfer.description:
Fritz Dopfer is a World Cup alpine ski racer for Germany, specializing in the technical events of giant slalom and slalom.
Born in Innsbruck, Austria, to a German father and an Austrian mother, the family lived in both countries during his youth. Wikipedia

Hubert Leitgeb.label: Hubert Leitgeb
Hubert Leitgeb.description:
Hubert Leitgeb was an Italian biathlete.
He won three medals at World Championships, including two golds. He competed in Biathlon World Cup, where he got 131 starts. In 1994 he had a World Cup victory in an individual competition. Wikipedia

Jure Šinkovec.label: Jure Sinkovec
Jure Šinkovec.description:
Jure Šinkovec is a Slovenian ski jumper who has competed in Ski jumping World Cup since 2005.
Šinkovec first podium in World Cup was in team competition in Harrachov HS 142m in December 2011. Wikipedia

MacKenzie Boyd-Clowes.label: MacKenzie Boyd-Clowes
MacKenzie Boyd-Clowes.description:
Mackenzie Boyd-Clowes is a Canadian ski jumper who has competed on the World Cup level since 2009.
He holds the Canadian ski jumping distance record of 205.0 metres which he jumped in Harrachov in 2013. Wikipedia

Marte Elden.label: Marte Elden
Marte Elden.description: Marte Elden is a Norwegian cross-country skier who has competed since 2005. Wikipedia

Matti Kuosku.label: Matti Kuosku
Matti Kuosku.description: Matti Kuosku was a Swedish cross-country skier. He competed in the Men's 50 kilometres event at the 1976 Winter Olympics. Wikipedia

Thobias Fredriksson.label: Thobias Fredriksson
Thobias Fredriksson.description: Thobias Fredriksson is a Swedish former cross-country skier who competed since 2000. He won two medals at the 2006 Winter Olympics in Turin with a gold in the team sprint and a bronze in the individual sprint events. Wikipedia

Stanisław Bobak.label: Stanisław Bobak
Stanisław Bobak.description:
Stanisław Bobak was a Polish ski jumper.
Bobak was born in Ząb. Stanisław Bobak was one of the leading ski jumpers of the 1970s and 1980s, and was a member of the Polish team at the 1976 Winter Olympics and 1980 Winter Olympics. He died in Zakopane. Wikipedia
